            <paragraph>Controls camera-specific attributes such as depth of field and exposure override.</paragraph>
            <paragraph>When used in a <reference internal="True" refuri="class_worldenvironment#class-worldenvironment"><inline classes="std std-ref">WorldEnvironment</inline></reference> it provides default settings for exposure, auto-exposure, and depth of field that will be used by all cameras without their own <strong>CameraAttributes</strong>, including the editor camera. When used in a <reference internal="True" refuri="class_camera3d#class-camera3d"><inline classes="std std-ref">Camera3D</inline></reference> it will override any <strong>CameraAttributes</strong> set in the <reference internal="True" refuri="class_worldenvironment#class-worldenvironment"><inline classes="std std-ref">WorldEnvironment</inline></reference>. When used in <reference internal="True" refuri="class_voxelgi#class-voxelgi"><inline classes="std std-ref">VoxelGI</inline></reference> or <reference internal="True" refuri="class_lightmapgi#class-lightmapgi"><inline classes="std std-ref">LightmapGI</inline></reference>, only the exposure settings will be used.</paragraph>
            <paragraph>See also <reference internal="True" refuri="class_environment#class-environment"><inline classes="std std-ref">Environment</inline></reference> for general 3D environment settings.</paragraph>
            <paragraph>This is a pure virtual class that is inherited by <reference internal="True" refuri="class_cameraattributesphysical#class-cameraattributesphysical"><inline classes="std std-ref">CameraAttributesPhysical</inline></reference> and <reference internal="True" refuri="class_cameraattributespractical#class-cameraattributespractical"><inline classes="std std-ref">CameraAttributesPractical</inline></reference>.</paragraph>
